  "description": {
    "en": {
      "provenance": "imported",
      "value": "Develop and implement training plans for partner NGOs including good governance, finance management\r\n\t\r\n\t\tTrain 4 NGO partners as well as government line agencies, service providers, networks, federation and alliance on women empowerment related issues including GED, RBA, Do-No-Harm, advocacy.\r\n\t\r\n\t\tTrain 300 PVSE groups and 135 Local Resource Persons\r\n\t\r\n\t\t\r\n\t\t\tSupport to PVSE women in diversification of on-farm and off-farm income\r\n\t\r\n\t\r\n\t\tSupport to PVSE women for improved land productivity\r\n\t\r\n\t\tLeasehold forest-management and community forest management\r\n\t\r\n\t\tVocational training to PVSE women\r\n\t\r\n\t\tParticipatory vulnerability assessment and contingency plan\r\n\t\r\n\t\tDistribution of emergency equipment and kits\r\n\t\r\n\t\tSmall-scale mitigation measures support\r\n\t\r\n\t\tFormation of community support groups and community support funds\r\n\t\r\n\t\tPromote reproductive health services via media and interpersonal communications as well as influence health facilities for better access and increased quality services according to the needs of PVSE women\r\n\t\r\n\t\tFacilitate mobile gynaecological services/ camps for uterus prolaps prevention and treatment\r\n\t\r\n\t\t\r\n\t\t\tStrengthen para-legal committees in Nawalparasi and establish paralegal committees in Chitwan and Makwanpur to provide counselling services to gender based violence survivors."
    },
    "ne": null
  },
